result.execSummary:
The defendant Rodrigo Eddie Gonzales was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Drive or Operate w/o Consent-Abandon Veh, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3m).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Rodrigo Eddie Gonzales in court with attorney Colleen Catherine Nordin.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minute sheet. State amends charge to Misdemeanor Operate M/V w/o Owners Consent, gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to amended charge.  Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds guilty of amended charge. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.

Defendant Rodrigo Eddie Gonzales in court with attorney Colleen Catherine Nordin.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file. Atty Nordin indicates restitution issue has been resolved, requests a 2 week adjournment so defendant can pay the remainder of the restitution and DA surcharge. State has no objection to adjournment. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for February 11, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Status conference scheduled for February 1, 2016 at 08:15 am.
